––– comment –––
Test HTTP Basic Auth authentication.
Spec: https://github.com/manticoresoftware/manticoresearch/blob/wip_auth/src/auth/spec.md
Issue: https://github.com/manticoresoftware/manticoresearch/issues/2983
Admin credentials: admin / adminpass (bootstrap via auth.json)

Per spec: Base64 encoded credentials, validation via sha256(salt + password)
Regression coverage: valid Basic auth succeeds, Basic scheme casing is accepted case-insensitively, malformed Basic auth returns a 401 response, and unknown users with supplied passwords report `using password: YES`.
––– comment –––
––– block: ../base/start-searchd-with-auth –––
––– comment –––
––– 1.2.1 Successful request with correct Basic Auth –––
EXPECTED: 200 OK with JSON result
––– comment –––
––– input –––
curl -s -u admin:adminpass -X POST http://127.0.0.1:9308/token -d "{}"
––– output –––
#!/\s*\{"token":"[0-9a-f]{64}"\}/!#
––– comment –––
––– 1.2.1a Successful request with lowercase Basic scheme –––
EXPECTED: 200 OK with JSON result
––– comment –––
––– input –––
curl -s -H "Authorization: basic YWRtaW46YWRtaW5wYXNz" -X POST http://127.0.0.1:9308/token -d "{}"
––– output –––
#!/\s*\{"token":"[0-9a-f]{64}"\}/!#
––– comment –––
––– 1.2.1b Successful request with uppercase Basic scheme –––
EXPECTED: 200 OK with JSON result
––– comment –––
––– input –––
curl -s -H "Authorization: BASIC YWRtaW46YWRtaW5wYXNz" -X POST http://127.0.0.1:9308/token -d "{}"
––– output –––
#!/\s*\{"token":"[0-9a-f]{64}"\}/!#
––– comment –––
––– 1.2.2 Reject with wrong password –––
EXPECTED: 401 Unauthorized with Access denied error
––– comment –––
––– input –––
curl -s -i -u admin:wrongpassword http://127.0.0.1:9308/sql -d "query=SELECT 1" | tr -d '\r' | awk '/^HTTP\/1.1|^\{"error":/ {print}'
––– output –––
HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized
{"error":"Access denied for user 'admin' (using password: YES)"}
––– comment –––
––– 1.2.3 Reject unknown user with supplied password –––
EXPECTED: 401 Unauthorized and using password: YES
––– comment –––
––– input –––
curl -s -i -u missing_user:sentpassword http://127.0.0.1:9308/sql -d "query=SELECT 1" | tr -d '\r' | awk '/^HTTP\/1.1|^\{"error":/ {print}'
––– output –––
HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized
{"error":"Access denied for user 'missing_user' (using password: YES)"}
––– comment –––
––– 1.2.4 Reject without Authorization header –––
EXPECTED: 401 Unauthorized with Basic auth challenge
––– comment –––
––– input –––
curl -s -i http://127.0.0.1:9308/sql -d "query=SELECT 1" | tr -d '\r' | awk '/^HTTP\/1.1|^WWW-Authenticate:|^\{"error":/ {print}'
––– output –––
HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized
WWW-Authenticate: Basic realm="Manticore daemon", charset="UTF-8"
{"error":"Authorization header field missed"}
––– comment –––
––– 1.2.5 Reject with invalid Base64 –––
EXPECTED: 401 Unauthorized with decode error response
––– comment –––
––– input –––
curl -s -i -H "Authorization: Basic not-valid-base64!!!" http://127.0.0.1:9308/sql -d "query=SELECT 1" | tr -d '\r' | awk '/^HTTP\/1.1|^\{"error":/ {print}'
––– output –––
HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized
{"error":"Failed to decode base64 user:password"}
